    Clips provide more consistent results in structured systems.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Where Most Gardeners Get It Wrong</h2>

  <h3>Using Clips That Are Too Strong</h3>
  <p>
    Can damage delicate stems.
  </p>

  <h3>Clipping Too Late</h3>
  <p>
    Makes alignment harder to correct.
  </p>

  <h3>Using Too Few Clips</h3>
  <p>
    Leads to uneven growth.
  </p>

  <h3>Ignoring Growth Speed</h3>
  <p>
    Cucumbers need frequent attention.
  </p>
</section>

